# ============================================================================
#  SmartTubular — set the Gemini voice-search API key (over adb)
# ============================================================================
#
#  Voice search uses Google's free Gemini API (the glasses' own speech
#  recognizer doesn't work for third-party apps). Typing a key on the glasses
#  isn't practical, and Android 14 blocks pushing files into the app's folder,
#  so the key is set with a single adb broadcast instead of a file.
#
#  STEP 1 — Get a free key:
#    https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey  (sign in, "Create API key", copy).
#    The free tier is plenty and needs no credit card.
#
#  STEP 2 — Send it to the app (replace YOUR_GEMINI_API_KEY, one command):
#
#    adb shell am broadcast -a org.smarttube.beta.cc.SET_GEMINI_KEY \
#      -n org.smarttube.beta.cc/com.liskovsoft.smartyoutubetv2.tv.ui.common.keyhandler.GeminiKeyReceiver \
#      --es key "YOUR_GEMINI_API_KEY"
#
#    You'll see a "Gemini key saved" toast on the glasses. The key is stored in
#    the app's private prefs. Do this once (re-do only if you reinstall or clear
#    app data).
#
#  STEP 3 — Open SmartTubular and tap the magnifying glass to search by voice.
#
#  OPTIONAL — change the model the same way (default is gemini-2.5-flash-lite,
#  which has the highest free-tier rate limit):
#
#    adb shell am broadcast -a org.smarttube.beta.cc.SET_GEMINI_KEY \
#      -n org.smarttube.beta.cc/com.liskovsoft.smartyoutubetv2.tv.ui.common.keyhandler.GeminiKeyReceiver \
#      --es model "gemini-2.5-flash"
#
#  SECURITY: the key only lives in app-private storage and your shell history.
#  If it leaks, rotate it at the aistudio link above and re-run STEP 2.
# ============================================================================
